The engagement of Linda Susan Pickens Huber to Victor Manuel Lopez-Balboa, a son of Mr. and Mrs. Enrique Lopez-Balboa of Montclair, N.J., has been announced by Mr. and Mrs. Harley L. Pickens of Princeton Junction, N.J., the parents of the bride-to-be.

Ms. Huber, an associate in the natural resources group of the First Boston Corporation in New York, graduated magna cum laude from Lehigh University and received an M.B.A. degree from Stanford University. She has been married and divorced. Her father, who is retired, was a major general in the Army Reserve and a systems analyst for RCA in Cherry Hill, N.J. Her mother, Eleanor A. Pickens, is the secretary to George W. Ball of Princeton, N.J., who was an Under Secretary of State in the Kennedy and Johnson Administrations.

The future bridegroom, a graudate of St. Mark's School and Columbia University, received an M.B.A. degree from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania and a J.D. degree from the Penn law school. He is an associate in mortgage finance at Goldman, Sachs & Company in New York.

His father is a senior managing director and the chief financial officer of the International Capital Corporation, a subsidiary of the American Express Bank in New York. His mother, Nancy C. Lopez-Balboa, is a professor of Spanish at Montclair State College.